org.eclipse.persistence.annotations

Annotation Type CopyPolicy


  • @Target(value=TYPE)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface CopyPolicy
    A CopyPolicy is used to set an org.eclipse.persistence.descriptors.copying.CopyPolicy on an Entity. It is required that a class that implements org.eclipse.persistence.descriptors.copying.CopyPolicy be specified as the argument. A CopyPolicy should be specified on an Entity, MappedSuperclass or Embeddable. For instance: @Entity @CopyPolicy("example.MyCopyPolicy")
    See Also:
    CopyPolicy, CloneCopyPolicy, InstantiationCopyPolicy
    Author:
    tware
